---
/**
 * rest-api/0010 · Figure 3 — polling vs webhook callback, side by side: polling
 * has the client repeatedly GET the server (simple, no client endpoint, but
 * wasteful and laggy); a webhook inverts it — the server POSTs a signed event to
 * the client (efficient, near-real-time push, but needs a public endpoint and
 * full delivery-semantic handling). Mature systems offer both.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source HTML (figure + svg + figcaption). Lives as an
 * .astro component for the kebab-case-SVG reason. The markers it references
 * (#arw, #arwG) come from the source's global hidden <svg>, which does not
 * travel with the figure, so they're inlined here in a local <defs>, fills/ids
 * verbatim.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 620 210"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Side by side: polling has the client repeatedly GET the server until done, simple but laggy; webhook has the server POST a callback to the client once, real-time but needs a public endpoint and delivery handling"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="310"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">TWO SHAPES, TWO TRADE-OFFS</text
            >
            <!-- POLLING -->
            <rect x="8" y="30" width="296" height="170" rx="10" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#d8d4c8"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="156"
                y="50"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">POLLING (202 + status)</text
            >
            <rect x="28" y="64" width="92" height="40" rx="8" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12"
            ></rect>
            <text x="74" y="88" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#7a1f12"
                >Client</text
            >
            <rect x="192" y="64" width="92" height="40" rx="8" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
            <text
                x="238"
                y="88"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">Server</text
            >
            <line x1="120" y1="76" x2="190" y2="76" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <text x="155" y="71" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
                >GET /jobs/123</text
            >
            <line x1="190" y1="92" x2="122" y2="92" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <text x="155" y="102" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
                >running… (again, again)</text
            >
            <text x="156" y="132" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >✓ dead simple · no client endpoint</text
            >
            <text x="156" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >✗ wasteful · laggy (next tick, not now)</text
            >
            <text x="156" y="176" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >Also: SSE / WebSockets / long-poll for</text
            >
            <text x="156" y="189" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >low-latency continuous updates.</text
            >
            <!-- WEBHOOK -->
            <rect x="316" y="30" width="296" height="170" rx="10" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#d8d4c8"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="464"
                y="50"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">WEBHOOK (callback)</text
            >
            <rect x="336" y="64" width="92" height="40" rx="8" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
            <text
                x="382"
                y="88"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">Server</text
            >
            <rect x="500" y="64" width="92" height="40" rx="8" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="546"
                y="88"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">Client</text
            >
            <line x1="428" y1="84" x2="498" y2="84" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
            <text x="463" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
                >POST event (signed)</text
            >
            <text x="464" y="132" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >✓ efficient · near-real-time push</text
            >
            <text x="464" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#9a2417"
                >✗ public endpoint · every delivery semantic</text
            >
            <text x="464" y="176" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >at-least-once · out-of-order · must</text
            >
            <text x="464" y="189" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >verify auth · block replays · ack fast</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Mature systems offer <strong>both</strong>: the webhook delivers the happy-path push; the
        pollable status resource is the fallback for missed deliveries and crash recovery.
        Belt-and-suspenders, not indecision.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
